Rule Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the paper proposes an algorithm to learn the structure of the rules that represent the system. The algorithm gives a small set of fuzzy rules that represent the original set of examples. 

Probabilistic Methods are present in the text as the algorithm is able to manage with fuzzy information, which is inherently probabilistic in nature. The algorithm is able to learn the structure of the rules that represent the system, which involves dealing with uncertainty and probability.
